1971. In a popular beach near the Tuscan port of Livorno establishment, the young mother Anna participated in a beauty contest, she wins easily. Her jealous husband Mario is angry all the attention she gets, her 8-year-old son Bruno put off by the whole thing. His younger sister Valeria is the only one who can enjoy the spectacle. The current time. Bruno gets an urgent visit from Valeria who tells him that their mother has cancer. Bruno tries to avoid a return to Livorno, but finally gives in, and the view of his sleeping mother in her hospital brings bittersweet memories.

